WRITING.TEXT:
From what I understood in the main story and exploring relics and talking to all the races. Spoiler for the main quest  gt;!Since the entire Galaxy is a simulation by the Atlas- and the Atlas being close to death. It began acting erradically and deployed the Sentinels as a security force into the Euclid galaxy. The Vy'keen fought them off over hundreds of years in the edges of the galaxy- It resulted in a Vy'keen victory and the sentinels retreated out of the galaxy to bide their time. But this had left the Vy'keen weakened and vulnerable. ! lt;
      gt;!This is when the Empire of the first spawn attacked the weakened Vy'keen. Ceasing their territories and becoming the sole dominant power of the Galaxy. But around the same time, the Korvax began their revolution by sacrificing a large amount of themselves as nanites into the Gek spawning pools. ! lt;
      gt;!During this civil war, the Sentinels struck back harder than ever to secure the Galaxy. They drove deep into the Empire, dismanteling cities and most traces of civilization as they reached the core of the Galaxy and the Gek homeworld. ! lt;
      gt;!Which brings us to the time the game takes place in. There is now a Sentinel precense on every planet and only sparse outposts, space stations and small hubs are allowed to exist anymore. The Korvax worship the Sentinels as gods, The Vy'keen hate them deeply but there is no organised resistance anymore. ! lt;  However I'd love an overhaul to how factions work. With actual territories carved up between them, frontlines that might move back and forth as wars are declared and ended. And to top it off- we should be allowed to join one of them to fight for their cause. Or be allowed to start our own player made factions and empires. I'd love to see groups of players be able to clean a planet of a Sentinel precense and re-establish civilization and take control of their own areas of space. This could eventually spark some player vs player warfare. Which would also mean we need an overhaul to frigate/Freighter warfare in space.
